The paper deals with data structures for representing trees, which is a fundamental topic in computer science. The paper proposes new succinct representations of ordinal trees and discusses their static and dynamic properties. This makes it likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also discusses range queries, which is a topic in computational geometry, making it likely to belong to the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. The paper also discusses entropy-bounded storage of dynamic sequences, which is a topic in information theory, making it likely to belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The paper also discusses compressed full-text self-indexes, which is a topic in data compression, making it likely to belong to the cs.DM (Data Compression) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses time complexity of operations, which is a topic in theoretical computer science, making it likely to belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category.
